      <title>India ready for world's biggest religious festival</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANIndia is all set for Kumbh Mela, the biggest religious festival in the world, beginning on January 15.The Indian town of Prayagraj, originally known as Allahabad, is getting ready for the annual Kumbh Mela festivities. Prayagraj will be the largest temporary city in the world during the festival, according to CNBC TV18.The festival of Kumbh Mela has also been added to UNESCO's list of "Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity," according to Times Now News.The Kumbh Mela celebrations takes place near the Triveni Sangam, which is where three sacred rivers in Hinduism meet together. People usually bathe in the water to wash off their sins.Preparations have been made so that devotees can pray at the "Akshay Vat," which is a sacred fig tree in Hinduism."Hindu monks that live in seclusion, often attend the Kumbh Mela to interact with the public and chant vedic mantras and play spiritual music.As many as 800 special trains will run to the city in order to prepare for the event, according to Times Now News. Airlines such as Air India have also announced flights to the holy city.The Kumbh Mela takes place over 55 days and will last until March 30.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Hindu saints marching at the Kumbh Mela2. The Triveni Sangam and a saint bathing in the river3. Akshay Vat, a sacred fig tree for Hindus4. Hindu monks marching and playing musicVOICEOVER (in English): "The Indian town of Prayagraj, originally known as Allahabad, is getting ready for the annual Kumbh Mela festivities which is set to begin on January 15.""The Kumbh Mela celebrations takes place near the Triveni Sangam, which is where three sacred rivers in Hinduism meet together. "People usually bathe in the water to wash off their sins.""Preparations have been made so that devotees can pray at the 'Akshay Vat,' which is a sacred fig tree in Hinduism.""Hindu monks that live in seclusion, often attend the Kumbh Mela to interact with the public and chant vedic  mantras and play spiritual music."SOURCES: Times Now News, NDTV, Live Mint, India.com, CNBC, https://www.timesnownews.com/india/article/kumbh-mela-2019-largest-temporary-city-of-world-uttar-pradesh-prayagraj-yogi-adityanath/343604https://www.timesnownews.com/india/article/kumbh-mela-prayagraj-ardh-kumbh-mela-2019-important-dates-how-to-reach-where-to-stay-all-you-need-to-know-kumbh-mela-2019-map-kumbh-mela-date-and/342354https://www.ndtv.com/allahabad-news/for-kumbh-2019-prayagraj-to-have-worlds-largest-temporary-city-1974408https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/up-minister-says-rs-4-300-crore-set-aside-for-kumbh-mela-preparations-1973243https://www.livemint.com/Opinion/5UCi9CpfeEfjCpdOIbSx0M/Opinion-The-Kumbh-Mela-Indias-first-smart-city-and-more.htmlhttps://www.india.com/news-travel/what-to-expect-at-the-maha-kumbh-mela-happening-in-prayagraj-3510110/https://www.cnbctv18.com/market/data/kumbh-mela-2019-millions-expected-at-worlds-biggest-festival-1883211.htm***]]></description>
