      <title>China monitors its citizens using AI-embedded CCTV cameras</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANChina has developed CCTV cameras embedded with artificial intelligence to track the movements of civilians across the country.The program, Ensemble Net, was trained using clips from CCTV footage and is supposedly 90 percent accurate, New Scientist reports.The system will be able to scan body shapes and facial features. It will then scan the database to see if it finds a match.The program will also be able to identify a person in disguise or if their back is faced towards the camera.The AI-powered CCTV cameras have already been used by Chinese authorities to track down fugitives, CNet reports.China plans to have over 600 million AI-powered CCTV cameras by 2020, according to Q Daily, a Chinese online publication.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Map of China, CCTV camera, and a CCTV camera surveilling people2. CCTV footage and a measurement bar3. A man's body and facial features being scanned4. The same man in a disguise and with his back faced towards the cameraVOICEOVER (in English): "New Scientist reports China has developed CCTV cameras embedded with artificial intelligence to track the movements of civilians across the country.""The program, Ensemble Net, was trained using clips from CCTV footage and is supposedly 90 percent accurate.""The system will be able to scan body shapes and facial features. It will then scan the database to see if it finds a match.""Apparently the program will also be able to identify a person in disguise or if their back is faced towards the camera."SOURCES: New Scientist, CNet, Q Daily https://www.newscientist.com/article/2191558-chinese-army-ai-can-track-people-across-different-cctv-cameras/https://www.cnet.com/news/ai-powered-cctv-cameras-in-china-catch-another-wanted-fugitive/https://www.qdaily.com/articles/47431.html***]]></description>
